Key design decisions in this assembly:

1. **Tauri v2 IPC**: All 8 commands (`create_note`, `save_note`, `read_note`, `list_notes`, `search_notes`, `delete_note`, `get_settings`, `update_settings`) are implemented in Rust with `#[tauri::command]`
2. **No denied plugins**: Only `tauri-plugin-dialog` is included; no fs/shell/http plugins
3. **Clipboard**: Uses browser `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` with `execCommand` fallback вЂ” no Tauri clipboard plugin
4. **CodeMirror 6**: Markdown syntax highlighting only, no preview/rendering
5. **Auto-save**: 500ms debounce via `EditorView.updateListener`
6. **Filename format**: `YYYY-MM-DDTHHMMSS.md`, immutable after creation
7. **YAML frontmatter**: Tags only, displayed with dimmed background in editor
8. **CSS columns masonry**: Pinterest-style grid with 3/2/1 column breakpoints
9. **Default 7-day filter**: Applied on initial load
10. **Full-text search**: Simple file-scan with case-insensitive substring matching, 300ms debounce
11. **Svelte 5 runes**: Uses `$state`, `$derived`, `$props` throughout
12. **SvelteKit static adapter**: `ssr = false`, `prerender = false` for Tauri WebView
